VALUES ('A value is rounded to 2 decimal places as 77.3.

What is the error interval for the original value?', '77.295 \le x < 77.30499999999999', ARRAY['77.28999999999999 \le x < 77.31', '77.295 < x \le 77.30499999999999', '77.295 \le x \le 77.30499999999999'], ARRAY['77.28999999999999 \le x < 77.31', '77.295 \le x \le 77.30499999999999', '77.295 \le x < 77.30499999999999', '77.295 < x \le 77.30499999999999'], 'Step 1: Rounding to 2 d.p. means the half-step is 0.005.

Step 2: Lower bound = 77.3 - 0.005 = 77.295.

